##### What’s Next for OpenArchive and the DAC Program

Through several phases of co-research, OpenArchive learned more about the unique contexts our DACs work in and gained a better understanding of their needs. 

Using findings from our co-research, we will continue to customize workshops and trainings and implement usability enhancements to our [**_Save_** app]. Over the next couple of years, we will also be adding several security features, including end-to-end encryption, to **_Save_** to better protect our users and their media as they work to document, preserve, and share evidence of human rights abuses. 

Contact us at info@open-archive.org to learn more about **_Save_** training opportunities. 

In the next few months, we will be publishing a research paper on the benefits and drawbacks of using decentralized web storage in repressive regions. This paper builds on our previous two blog posts on [Mapping the Decentralized Web Ecosystem](https://open-archive.org/news/mapping-the-decentralized-storage-ecosystem) and [Harm Reduction for History’s First Responders](https://open-archive.org/news/harm-reduction-for-historys-first-responders)xn. If you are interested in keeping up with our work, please stay in touch!

